cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the design of more effective basic units for neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of the elastic collision model in physics as inspiration for the proposed structure suggests a potential connection to the field of computational physics (cs.NE). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on improving performance for image classification tasks, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
